headline: Coinbase Tops Earnings Views, But Misses Estimates On Key Metrics
summary: The cryptocurrency exchange on Wednesday announced a partnership with JPMorgan and received a pair of major price hikes earlier this week as the Trump administration's digital asset policy takes shape.  Coinbase reported earnings of $5.14 per share, up from 14 cents per share last year, on a slight uptick in revenue to $1.5 billion.  Transaction revenue was $764 million for the quarter, down from $781 million a year ago and $1.26 billion in Q1, respectively.
